Head with eyes distinctly narrower than width of prothorax (width prothorax/head 1.24-1.54). Rostrum long, 1.7-2.1 wider than long (Group2), or shorter, 2.4-2.75 (in Group 3 species), or short, 2.55-3.15 (Group 1 species). Maxillary palps short (Group 2 species) or long (Groups 1 and 3 species), apical palpomeres cylindrical with truncate apices; galea moderately long and narrow, or long and narrow (Group 1 species, and in
A. hirtipes
